{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":6904,"name":"","username":"christianclavet","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/c/76d3ee/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-07-25T20:33:58.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHi! I‚Äôm really new to URHO3D and just discovered it recently. This project is really incredible with all the features that I always wanted!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI would like to create an editor with URHO3D similar to the one I‚Äôve worked on. (Working and learning on this for the last 5 years). It used Irrlicht as render/gui. (\u003ca href=\"http://irrrpgbuilder.sourceforge.net\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttp://irrrpgbuilder.sourceforge.net\u003c/a\u003e)\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"http://irrrpgbuilder.sourceforge.net/forum/download/file.php?id=180\u0026amp;t=1\" title=\"\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"http://irrrpgbuilder.sourceforge.net/forum/download/file.php?id=180\u0026amp;t=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"690\" height=\"401\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e800√ó465\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis is a simple game editor as I‚Äôm not a real programmer, but learning programming as a hobbyist. URHO3D save me  a lot of complexities has all the needed features are there, and I don‚Äôt think I would need to add other libs/framework to it to redo the game editor.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI would need to add specific GUIs to the URHO3D gui. I‚Äôve searched in the forum and on google but did not found more information on how to add custom GUIs.\u003cbr\u003e\nBasically, I would need to create in C++ without patching URHO3D:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003elua code editor with highlighting. Highlighting could be added later. If we can type in multiline would do first, then I could add features. (Would like to add to the URho3D gui)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTabbed GUI component. I don‚Äôt like menus and would use this instead.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSo is there some way of doing a new GUI component (C++) and use it directly from my application with the URHO3D gui? Looking from the editor you seem to have a ‚Äúgeneric‚Äù UIelement, and it look possible. So could I create a new class using the base UIElement in my application or it would be required that new UIElements be added in URHO3D sources and recompiled?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFor the rest, the GUI is more than adequate, the URHO editor showed me a lot of nice stuff!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFor now, I‚Äôve just compiled URHO and checking it. So I have lots of things to learn! The current GUI system is ok for me, I just need to be able to ‚Äúplug‚Äù my own to it and I don‚Äôt like patching. I will also have to learn how git is working, I‚Äôm only familiar with SVN.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:06:06.733Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":205,"reads":18,"readers_count":17,"score":1028.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":1214,"topic_slug":"can-new-guis-be-created-without-patching","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://irrrpgbuilder.sourceforge.net","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"IrrRPG Builder","clicks":5},{"url":"http://irrrpgbuilder.sourceforge.net/forum/download/file.php?id=180\u0026t=1","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":171,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":6906,"name":"","username":"thebluefish","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/t/f04885/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-07-26T02:40:12.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eCreate a class that derives from UIComponent and do everything there.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFor example, \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/thebluefish/Urho3DEditor/blob/master/Prime/GameClient/src/UI/TabWindow.h\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehere‚Äôs Scorvi‚Äôs tab control\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAs far a text editor, that‚Äôs a bit more advanced. Honestly in that regard I‚Äôd look at integrating some third party UI, such as \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/fruxo/turbobadger\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eTurbo Badger\u003c/a\u003e. It‚Äôs a bit more advanced integrating a third-party library, but it will allow you to leverage much more mature libraries.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:06:06.855Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":5,"reads":17,"readers_count":16,"score":28.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":1214,"topic_slug":"can-new-guis-be-created-without-patching","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/thebluefish/Urho3DEditor/blob/master/Prime/GameClient/src/UI/TabWindow.h","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":21},{"url":"https://github.com/fruxo/turbobadger","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - fruxo/turbobadger: Small footprint UI library for hardware accelerated games \u0026 applications","clicks":9}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":80,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":6907,"name":"","username":"rasteron","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/rasteron/{size}/55_2.png","created_at":"2015-07-26T04:38:59.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI also did a Tab Menu Component workaround and example wayback. This was tested with older versions but since this was done purely via angelscript and xml layout files, it does not require tinkering with engine code and should work on the latest Editor code with some slight or no modifications at all.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-MbXzSUHaJo4/UlLCnXO6xFI/AAAAAAAAADg/WrK4cyxdgPE/s400/tabmenu.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"330\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOriginal Thread and Files\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/urho3d/7IKM_UJndOg\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003egroups.google.com/forum/#!topic ‚Ä¶ IKM_UJndOg\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e*Patch is just for angelscript files only to automate the process but you can manually do those edits without problems.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:06:06.930Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":18,"readers_count":17,"score":18.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":1214,"topic_slug":"can-new-guis-be-created-without-patching","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/urho3d/7IKM_UJndOg","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Google Groups","clicks":4}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":54,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":6915,"name":"","username":"christianclavet","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/c/76d3ee/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-07-26T18:57:15.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eWow! Thanks! So it can be done! I‚Äôm really happy about this!  \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/smiley.png?v=9\" title=\":smiley:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":smiley:\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nThanks for all the links. I‚Äôll only start first at deriving the class and see how it work. The code editor can be simple at first, as I‚Äôm no hurry. Once I know more how to use Urho, I might try to put that library (the screenshot of the GUI was really beautiful!)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIs there a URHO guide somewhere on how to make skins for the GUI? The current editor is really nice for the functionalities it offer, but would need little tweaks on the design in my opinion. The icons are really too small for the resolution we have today. (The icons size seem to be from the 1024x768 era, where we have 2K and 4K monitors today)\u003cbr\u003e\nIf we compare with Unreal editor, check the icon size they have:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cimg src=\"http://i1.wp.com/blog.digitaltutors.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Interface.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"\" height=\"\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:06:07.489Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":6,"reads":18,"readers_count":17,"score":33.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":1214,"topic_slug":"can-new-guis-be-created-without-patching","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":171,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":6921,"name":"","username":"boberfly","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/b/aeb1de/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-07-27T02:13:06.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHi,\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFrom memory there‚Äôs one texture atlas Textures/UI.png and an xml file which defines the offsets. You could, for instance, 2x the texture but then the offsets are pixel-aligned and not based on points.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/Data/UI/DefaultStyle.xml\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttps://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/Data/UI/DefaultStyle.xml\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFrom the docs:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"http://urho3d.github.io/documentation/1.4/_u_i.html\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttp://urho3d.github.io/documentation/1.4/_u_i.html\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSo yeah, it would need to be patched so that it doesn‚Äôt use integers (IntRect) but rather floating point normalized to the screen co-ords perhaps?\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/Source/Urho3D/UI/BorderImage.h\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttps://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/Source/Urho3D/UI/BorderImage.h\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(at the bottom).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOr BYO libRocket/imgui/TurboBadger/nanovg-based GUI and hook up Urho3D‚Äôs resource/events/gfx/etc.? I‚Äôve recently played around with kivy (a touch/UI framework for python that also works on mobile) and that brings some nice concepts too, but it‚Äôs python‚Ä¶\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:06:07.914Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":15,"readers_count":14,"score":3.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":1214,"topic_slug":"can-new-guis-be-created-without-patching","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://urho3d.github.io/documentation/1.4/_u_i.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Urho3D - Documentation","clicks":1},{"url":"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/Data/UI/DefaultStyle.xml","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Urho3D/DefaultStyle.xml at master ¬∑ urho3d/Urho3D ¬∑ GitHub","clicks":1},{"url":"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/Source/Urho3D/UI/BorderImage.h","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Urho3D/BorderImage.h at master ¬∑ urho3d/Urho3D ¬∑ GitHub","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":69,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":6924,"name":"","username":"codingmonkey","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/codingmonkey/{size}/119_2.png","created_at":"2015-07-27T08:02:09.000Z","cooked":"\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe icons are really too small for the resolution we have today\u003cbr\u003e\nfor my 1080p the icons size it‚Äôs ok. and am do not like unreal style menus there is a lot strange and useless things - they close view, and these biggest icons it‚Äôs awful, yes this is biggest icons in editor that‚Äôs why i‚Äôm do not install UE4  yet  \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/laughing.png?v=5\" title=\":laughing:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":laughing:\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nIMO better to use a lot of shortcuts than this.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:06:08.152Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":15,"readers_count":14,"score":8.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":1214,"topic_slug":"can-new-guis-be-created-without-patching","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":148,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":6925,"name":"","username":"rasteron","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/rasteron/{size}/55_2.png","created_at":"2015-07-27T10:06:02.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIf icon sizes or resolution is an issue, perhaps it‚Äôs time to consider and include SVG rendering for images/sprites. For starters, I found these libraries which supports SDL2 and cross platform‚Ä¶\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/bazzinotti/MultiPlatformSVGRenderer\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003egithub.com/bazzinotti/MultiPlatformSVGRenderer\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"http://www.linuxmotors.com/SDL_svg/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003elinuxmotors.com/SDL_svg/\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:06:08.216Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":14,"readers_count":13,"score":2.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":1214,"topic_slug":"can-new-guis-be-created-without-patching","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://www.linuxmotors.com/SDL_svg/","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"SDL_svg library","clicks":1},{"url":"https://github.com/bazzinotti/MultiPlatformSVGRenderer","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - bazzinotti/MultiPlatformSVGRenderer","clicks":1}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":54,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":6928,"name":"","username":"boberfly","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/b/aeb1de/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-07-28T01:57:29.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003e[quote=‚Äúrasteron‚Äù]If icon sizes or resolution is an issue, perhaps it‚Äôs time to consider and include SVG rendering for images/sprites. For starters, I found these libraries which supports SDL2 and cross platform‚Ä¶\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/bazzinotti/MultiPlatformSVGRenderer\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e://\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003egithub\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e.\u0